      {
        "hadithnumber": 1499,
        "arabicnumber": 1499,
        "text": "Narrated Abu Kibash:\"I brought a Jadha' sheep to Al-Madinah (for sale) but it remained with me. I saw Abu Hurairah and I asked him about it, so he said: 'I heard the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) saying: \"The best male\" - or - \"female Udhiyah is that from the Jadha' sheep.\" He said: \"So the people took note of that (they became interested in buying)",
        "grades": [
          {
            "name": "Ahmad Muhammad Shakir",
            "grade": "Daif"
          },
          {
            "name": "Al-Albani",
            "grade": "Daif"
